{
  "text": "In this equation, G F is the Fermi coupling constant, determined from the muon lifetime, and the g \u03b3 \u01eb\u00b5 specify the scalar, vector and tensor couplings between \u00b5-handed muons and \u01eb-handed electrons. Deviations from this expression due to the non-local nature of the standard model weak interaction are O(m non-zero in left-right symmetric models [5] . For recent reviews of muon decay, see [CITATION_1] 7, 8] .",
